## Usage in your page.tsx file

Now you can use this reusable component in different ways:

### Basic usage with props:

```tsx
import Popover from "@/components/Popover/Popover";

export default function MyPage() {
  return (
    <div>
      <Popover
        title="Custom Title"
        description="This is a customized popover description."
      />
    </div>
  );
}
```

### Advanced usage with custom trigger and content:

```tsx
import Popover from "@/components/Popover/Popover";

export default function MyPage() {
  return (
    <div>
      <Popover
        trigger={<button className="custom-button">Click me</button>}
        title="Custom Notifications"
      >
        <div className="custom-content">
          <p>You can add any content here</p>
          <button>Action button</button>
        </div>
      </Popover>
    </div>
  );
}
```

### Fully customized usage with direct component access:

```tsx
import Popover from "@/components/Popover/Popover";

export default function MyPage() {
  return (
    <Popover.Root>
      <Popover.Trigger className="my-custom-trigger">
        Custom Trigger
      </Popover.Trigger>
      <Popover.Portal>
        <Popover.Positioner>
          <Popover.Popup>
            <Popover.Arrow />
            <Popover.Title>Fully Custom Title</Popover.Title>
            <div>Any custom content!</div>
          </Popover.Popup>
        </Popover.Positioner>
      </Popover.Portal>
    </Popover.Root>
  );
}
```

This approach gives you multiple ways to use the component with different levels of customization while maintaining the styling and behavior.
