    gap: 0.5rem;
    font-size: 1rem;
    line-height: 1.5rem;
    color: var(--color-gray-900);
}

/* Rest of your CSS */
```

However, this approach is less maintainable as you'd have to repeat the variables in each component.

## Check for Path Issues

Make sure the path to your theme.css file is correct. If it's in a different location than what you're importing, adjust the import path accordingly.

With these changes, your CSS variables should be correctly applied to your Checkbox component, fixing both the checkbox appearance and the defaultChecked behavior we discussed earlier.
